    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>135100</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cherstich2009"/>, fig. <citedRange>143</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.30</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_βης"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">βης</seg></name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_σιος" type="patronymic"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F"><unclear>σ</unclear>ίω</seg></name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>bès fils de <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>sios.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>bes son of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>sios</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
                <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>bes figlio di <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>sios.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>This much mutilated base shows a man's name with a rather rare ending. The most plausible restoration would be <foreign xml:lang="grc">Εὐσέβης</foreign>,
               although this name, meaning 'Pious', is not very usual before the Roman imperial period. On the other hand, the father's name ended with -sios, for 
               which there are a lot of possibilities. It is thus impossible to offer any restitution.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
